For those of you who like to mentally prepare themselves for the hardships they have to endure before the workout like me:
3 sets (abs, booty, abs & booty)
27 exercises total, 30 secs on
SET 1:
▪︎ Russian twist chop
▪︎ Bicycle crunch
-- 10 second break --
▪︎ Corkscrew
▪︎ Alternative toe touch
-- 10 second break --
▪︎ Side plank crunch (L)
▪︎ Side plank crunch (R)
-- 10 second break --
▪︎ U boat
▪︎ Heel touches
-- 10 second break --
▪︎ Spiderman plank
▪︎ Plank tap
-- 15 second break--
SET 2:
▪︎ Fire hydrant kick (L)
▪︎ Fire hydrant kick (R)
-- 10 second rest --
▪︎ U-raise (L)
▪︎ U-raise (R)
-- 5 second rest --
▪︎ Side-plank hip abduction (L)
▪︎ Side-plank hip abduction (R)
-- 5 second rest --
▪︎ Single leg glute bridge (L)
▪︎ Single leg glute bridge (R)
-- 5 second rest --
▪︎ Booty flutters
▪︎ Booty tap
-- 10 second rest --
SET 3:
▪︎ In & Out
▪︎ Glute bridges
-- 5 second rest --
▪︎ Plank kickback (L)
▪︎ Plank kickback (R)
-- 5 second rest --
▪︎ Donkey kick hydrant (L)
▪︎ Donkey kick hydrant (R)
-- 5 second rest --
▪︎ Booty tap
DONE!! CONGRATS!! 🥳🥳🥳

snippet.textDisplay:
I came to the conclusion 4 days ago I can either continue to be unhealthy or have a body glow up during this quarantine and I chose the second option so I'm doing the hourglass programme. Some things I have learnt so far: my hands starts sweating a lot in the middle so I LITERALLY have to stop working out and wash my hands then continue on. Another thing is that I sweat A Lot, places I didn't know I sweat maybe too much info but who cares. Also I can't do any type of plank but I am getting better at it, as in after 4 days I could hold it for 15 seconds.
Day 1- It was.. ok? As in I didn't feel like completely dying until the 10 minutes shred workout which I am kinda confused about. But planks, well that's a different situation. I cannot, repeating it, CANNOT do planks to save my life so hopefully I'll get better.
Day 2- I sweat like I am trying to fill a pool, like seriously. My arms were also hurting, I was kinda excited to do the hip dips workout because it's new but 10 minute shred thing again I found it hard, really hard.
Day 4- Again sweating, A LOT but I can hold planks better I would like to say, maybe not always correctly but i can hold it if that makes sense, as in I forget to engage my core. Ummm I also kinda have to wash my hands because I sweat so much that I start slipping when I'm doing planks or I don't know the In and Out exercise. I'm also kinda surprised I'm carrying this on, only because I really though 'oh I might do this for what one or two days' but here we are. I think it's mainly because I feel like have nothing else to do which is true cuz we're on easter break in the UK right now so no school either and also lockdown.

snippet.textDisplay:
So I wanted to try this workout out and track my progress over the course of the next 20 days. Right now I am 5'4", 118 lbs, but I want to get back to my summer bod, 110 lbs, and get a bigger booty, a slimmer waist, and more defined abs. I thought I would give this workout a try. For comparison, I've done the Alexis Ten 10-minute abs and 10-minute beach butt workouts multiple times and found those much more difficult than this one. I think I might do both, or just continue with this one, because I already go to track practice 5-6 times a week and I don't want to be sore for practice. I'll update you guys on my journey. Good luck you beautiful sexy animals.

Day 1: workout was easy and I didn't need any breaks. I liked the butterfly butt toe-touching thing. I think I'll modify some of the exercises to make them harder.
